headline: Lockheed Delivers Steady Defense Profits as Boeing Burns Billions Ramping Production
summary: Boeing (NYSE: BA) and Lockheed Martin (NYSE: LMT) reported Q3 2025 earnings in late October, revealing two aerospace giants in completely different financial realities. Boeing delivered its strongest aircraft volume since 2018 while bleeding billions. Lockheed beat estimates with $6.95 EPS after a catastrophic Q2 miss. One Turns Cash Positive.
